26. Verba fiunt mortuo] ‘ You are wasting your words on the dead ς’ you have a bad listener. The Greek proverb is quoted: νεκρῷ μύθους εἰς οὖς λέγεις. Erasmus accounts for the proverb by the common custom of calling on the dead after their breath had left them, and when they were said to be ‘conclamati.’ But this is not a correct account of that custom. See note on Eunuchus ii. 3. 55.
